{"lemma":"عَرّاف","slug":"عَرّاف","root":"ع.ر.ف","root_slug":"ع-ر-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ر-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28749"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%91%D8%A7%D9%81"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"diviner, fortuneteller"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From عَرَفَ (ʕarafa, “to know”)."},"ipa":["/ʕar.raːf/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28749","headword_ar":"عَرَّافٌ","root":"Erf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAhin","text_ar":"كَاهِن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diviner"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, O, Msb, K:) or the former is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who informs of the past,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter is one who informs of the past and of the future: (Msb:) or, accord. to Er-Rághib, [but the converse of his explanation seems to be that which is correct,] the former is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who informs of future events,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter is one who informs of past events. (TA.) Hence the saying of the Prophet, that whoso comes to an"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Er~Af","text_ar":"عرّاف"},{"kind":"text","text":"and asks him respecting a thing, prayer of forty nights will not be accepted from him. (O.) ―         -b2-  And (Msb)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An astrologer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who lays claim to the knowledge of hidden,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"invisible, things,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which God has made to belong exclusively to Himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth:) and this is [said to be] meant in the trad. above mentioned. (Mgh.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A physician."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who smells"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ysm","text_ar":"يسم"},{"kind":"text","text":"I read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya$um~u","text_ar":"يَشُمُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the ground, and thus knows the places of water, and knows in what country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"district, he is."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, in TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HzY","text_ar":"حزى"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","IAth","Mgh"]}]}}